Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @pork belly{400%g} on both sides with a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. When hot, carefully add the pork belly to the pan, skin-side down, and sear until golden, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Pop a large #saucepan{} of @water{} on to boil for your pasta.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1/2}(peeled). Pick the @thyme{1}(leaves picked from stalks, discard stalks). Crush the @black peppercorns{1}(crushed in a #freezer bag{}) in a #saucepan{}. When your water boils, add the @penne pasta{100%g} and a large pinch of @salt{}. Cook for ~{12%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}. Rinse out the pan to use for the sauce!

When the pork is golden all over, transfer to a #baking tray{}, skin-side up. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through ~{45-60%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Wipe out the frying pan with some #kitchen paper{} and return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the pan is hot, add the shallot and mushrooms. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they begin to colour, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in half the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute}. Off the heat, add the @reduced fat creme fraiche{150%g}, all of the cheddar, half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and half the thyme. Stir in the wheat pasta. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Tip the cheesy wheat pasta into an #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the @panko breadcrumbs{10g} and the remaining Italian style cheese and thyme.

When the pork has ~{10%minutes} left, bake the cheesy pasta bake on the top shelf of the oven until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in the saucepan you used for the pasta over medium heat. Add the peppercorns and fry for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{150%ml} and @red wine stock paste{14%g}. Stir to dissolve, bring to the boil and bubble for ~{3-5%minutes}. Wipe out the frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a splash of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}. Add the @baby spinach{125%g} and cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once everything is ready, sprinkle the @truffle zest{1}(sprinkled) over the wheat pasta bake (it's quite strong - you can always add more once you've tasted it!) and spoon onto plates. Pop the spinach alongside. Slice the pork belly, arrange on top of the spinach and finish with the peppercorn jus. Enjoy!